OL,6,FOne asylum seeker who was in the hotel
OL,7,Fat the time told ITV News: "I'm not
OL,8,Fsorry for him. I want him to learn
OL,9,Flessons for the future. If he had
OL,10,Fburned the building I would never have
OL,11,Fseen my mother and father again."
OL,13,FBirley's sentence is three years
OL,14,Flonger than any other term handed out
OL,15,Fin connection with the rioting to date.
OL,17,FAs well as his prison sentence, Birley
OL,18,Fwill serve an extended period of five
OL,19,Fyears on licence.
